sec.p:
Although he grew up in a family of health care specialists, he was hired as a 17-year-old high school junior by Coast Federal Savings & Loan of Los Angeles (now merged with 

Bank of the West
) to deliver patriotic speeches to rotary clubs, churches, veterans’ groups and other organizations.  He was paid $50 a speech plus gas mileage and $1 for every audience member. He often earned hundreds of dollars each week, far more than his fellow classmates who earned a buck or two an hour stocking store shelves.
